<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 11 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTO-1X707LL/DLL/MLL AND RTO-1X709MLL MODELS - INSTALL - AUXILIARY
        SECTION
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="4">
        <title>AUXILIARY SECTION</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>There are different bolt lengths; install in the correct location.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Auxiliary sections can be installed either with the transmission in the horizontal position or the
                    vertical position.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>To install in the vertical position, the clutch housing must be installed.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <para>To install the auxiliary section in the horizontal position.</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position a new gasket on the transmission mounting surface (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020o9">Figure 249</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020o9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020o9" filename="../figg13/G13020o9.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 249. Attach Hanger Bracket</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach an auxiliary section hanger bracket to the auxiliary section top (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020o9">Figure 249</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach a lifting chain to the auxiliary section hanger bracket (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020o9">Figure 249</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the auxiliary section on the two (2) dowel pins (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020o9">Figure 249</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the auxiliary section on until the hanger bracket contacts the front section back (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020o9">Figure 249</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the auxiliary section hanger bracket.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen the retaining covers (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020p0">Figure 250</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020p0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020p0" filename="../figg13/G13020p0.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 250. Loosen Retaining Covers</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the auxiliary section the rest of the way into position (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020p0">Figure 250</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply Eaton/Fuller Sealant #71205 or Loctite 242 to the retaining bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020p0">Figure 250</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the retaining bolts and tighten to 35 to 45 ft-lbs. (47 to 61 N&#8226;m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020p0">Figure 250</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To finish the installation, refer to
                <hotlnk document="s13020_HL1302008.xml" xrefid="hl1302008">SHIMMING PROCEDURE FOR TAPERED
                    BEARINGS</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <para>To install the auxiliary section in the vertical position.</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With blocks under the clutch housing to prevent input shaft damage, place the transmission
                in the vertical position, clutch housing down.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position a new gasket on the transmission mounting surface.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a steel bar through the yoke (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020p1">Figure 252</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020p2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020p1" filename="../figg13/G13020p1.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 251. Steel Bar Through Yoke</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach a lifting chain to the steel bar (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020p1">Figure 252</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the auxiliary section over the two (2) dowel pins (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020p1">Figure 252</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the auxiliary section down the dowels.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen the retaining covers (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020p1">Figure 252</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the auxiliary section the rest of the way into position (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020p1">Figure 252</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020p1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020p2" filename="../figg13/G13020p2.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 252. Install Retaining Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply Eaton/Fuller Sealant #71205 or Loctite 242 to the retaining bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020p1">Figure 252</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the retaining bolts; tighten to 35 to 45 ft-lbs. (47 to 61 N&#8226;m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020p1">Figure 252</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the steel bar and chain.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To finish the installation, refer to
                <hotlnk document="s13020_HL1302008.xml" xrefid="hl1302008">SHIMMING PROCEDURE FOR TAPERED
                    BEARINGS</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
